results.name: Number of subsets of {1, 2, ..., n} containing n and having <=5 pairwise coprime elements.
link: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..200
example: a(10) = 12 because there are 12 subsets of {1, 2, ..., 10} containing 10 and having <=5 pairwise coprime elements: {10}, {1,10}, {3,10}, {7,10}, {9,10}, {1,3,10}, {1,7,10}, {1,9,10}, {3,7,10}, {7,9,10}, {1,3,7,10}, {1,7,9,10}. There is no subset with exactly 5 elements here.
xref: Column 5 of triangle A186975. Sum of A186988 and A186976.
